summary: ...IMELDA FORECAST TO BECOME A HURRICANE TOMORROW MORNING... ...TROPICAL STORM CONDITIONS CONTINUE OVER THE ABACOS... As of 8:00 PM EDT Mon Sep 29 the center of Imelda was located near 28.1, -77.3 with movement N at 9 mph. The minimum central pressure was 985 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 65 mph.
